'''Ellen Petri''' (born 25 May 1982 in [[Merksem]], [[Antwerp]]) is a Belgian [[beauty pageant]] titleholder who was crowned [[Miss Belgium|Miss Belgium 2004]] on 12 December 2003.

==Biography==
At nine-years-old, Petri began practicing [[ballet]] and is employed as a model and choreographer.

In October 2004 she won a 'Sims Award' as the model with the nicest personality.  She won the contest 'The Heavenly 100' organized by the Flanders' magazine 'Ché' in 2004. She was voted the most beautiful woman on Earth. Second was [[Beyoncé]].   She won the 'Top Fashion Designer Award' at the [[Miss World 2004]] pageant.   She reached third place in the "World's Top Model" (won by Miss Mexico).<ref name="topm">(24 November 2004). [http://www.nieuwsblad.be/article/detail.aspx?articleid=G93AF4D6 Ellen Petri derde in Miss World Top Model], ''[[Het Nieuwsblad]]'' (in Dutch)</ref>

