{{LincolnSeries}}
The '''Lincoln family''' includes all the descendants of [[Abraham Lincoln]] and [[Mary Todd Lincoln]].
There are ten known descendants of Lincoln. The family line is believed to have been extinct since its last undisputed descendant, [[Robert Todd Lincoln Beckwith]], died on December 24, 1985, without any children.{{refn|Robert's second wife did have a son, named [[Timothy Lincoln Beckwith]], and listed Robert as the father, which would make Timothy Abraham Lincoln's great-great-grandson and only living descendant. Robert denied paternity of the child, claimed he had undergone a [[vasectomy]] years earlier, and a divorce court ruled that Robert was not the father.|group=nb}} It is rumored that there may be additional living descendants, but scholars disagree as to the legitimacy of these claims. However, the Lincoln family does have other surviving relatives who share common ancestors with the former president. One example is [[Ben Miller]], who after doing research has found a genealogical link to the Lincolns.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p038xdzt |title=Ben Miller finds out an amazing fact, Series 10, Coming Home |first=Ben |last=Miller |publisher=BBC One |website=BBC |access-date=May 16, 2017 |date=November 23, 2015 }}</ref>

