'''Valeriu D. Cotea''' (May 11, 1926&ndash;April 21, 2016) was a [[Romania]]n [[oenologist]]. From 1976 to 2000, Cotea represented Romania at the [[International Organisation of Vine and Wine]], based in [[Paris]]. He founded and led the [[Iași]]-based Oenology Research Centre of the [[Romanian Academy]], based in [[Iași]]. He was elected a titular member of the Academy in 1993. Cotea died in Iași in 2016 following [[cardiac arrest]] provoked by choking on a slice of orange.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stefan|first1=Borcea|title=A murit "patriarhul" vinului românesc, academicianul vrâncean Valeriu D. Cotea|url=http://adevarul.ro/locale/focsani/a-murit-patriarhul-vinului-romanesc-academicianul-vrancean-valeriu-d-cotea-1_571882275ab6550cb8347455/index.html|website=adevarul.ro|accessdate=23 April 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ZI DE DOLIU: S-a stins din viaţă academicianul Valeriu Cotea. A stat cinci zile internat|url=http://www.ziaruldeiasi.ro/stiri/zi-de-doliu-s-a-stins-din-viata-academicianul-valeriu-cotea-a-stat-cinci-zile-internat--125732.html|website=ziaruldeiasi.ro|accessdate=23 April 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref>  He was 89.

